# @@AGENT_VAULT_CA_PEM@@ — placeholder so ./agent-vault-ca.pem resolves; the build flow overwrites it.
# `just bootstrap` fetches GET http://metal:14321/v1/mitm/ca.pem once metal is up and writes the real
# PUBLIC CA into the gitignored .build copy before building the hermes image — this tracked file stays
# a placeholder, so the repo carries no per-deployment cert. A CA public cert is not a secret.
# `nix flake check` reads the path literally and security.pki.certificateFiles installs it into the
# hermes VM's OS trust store. To pin a CA in-tree instead, replace this file with the real
# -----BEGIN CERTIFICATE----- block.
